29:["$","p",null,{"className":"x:not-first:mt-[1.25em] x:leading-7","children":["Workspace bus plugins use Node.js dynamic imports (",["$","code",null,{"className":"nextra-code","dir":"ltr","children":"import()"}],"). The Node module loader caches imports. Replacing a cached module requires restarting the process — there is no safe way to hot-reload a module in a running Node/Bun process without risking stale closure references."]}]
2a:["$","p",null,{"className":"x:not-first:mt-[1.25em] x:leading-7","children":["Pi SDK extensions bypass this by using the Pi SDK’s own extension runtime, which has first-class support for dynamic tool registration via ",["$","code",null,{"className":"nextra-code","dir":"ltr","children":"pi.registerTool()"}],". The Pi SDK is designed for interactive use where adding tools at runtime is a core feature."]}]
